{
  "stem": "2996.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He had his own Yeshiva, which is a place where you train people to become rabbis.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was the first one to be named after that famous rabbi, Maharam Shik.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He died in 1880s-- in 1879.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my father was the first grandchild after him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So he was named after him-- Moishe.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Um--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Always.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know exactly whether I understood you correctly.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh yes, learned people, who really know not only the history about the birth of the Israel or anything like that-- the learned people and who are Orthodox, if I say to them, I'm a descendant of the Maharam Shik, they say what is called a Shehecheyanu, which is a prayer, which thanks God for this moment that I had an opportunity to witness this, whether this particular thing or something else.",
      "word_count": 72
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So [LAUGHS] one so-called rabbi was not a good human being.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was a dishonest man.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And part of my job, about which I will speak later-- part of my job was to keep our skirts clean-- our meaning the skirts of the Jewish community, the individuals in the Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had word that this particular rabbi was in San Francisco and was what might be called a ganef.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was not an honest man.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I tricked him, in a way, to come to see me, where I was going to read him the Riot Act.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he came.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So the secretary says, Rabbi So-and-So is out there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I say, yeah, send him in.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he said two words.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I knew immediately, oh ho, a Hungarian accent.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I told him how I'm a descendant of the Maharam Shik.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he was about to say the Shehecheyanu, which I explained before what it is.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
